SIMPLE: monarchy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monarchy
<hw>Mon"arch*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Monarchies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F. <ets>monarchie</ets>,
L. <ets>monarchia</ets>, Gr. <?/. See <er>Monarch</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A state or government in which the supreme power is
lodged in the hands of a monarch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A system of government in which the chief ruler is a
monarch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In those days he had affected zeal for <qex>monarchy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The territory ruled over by a monarch; a
kingdom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What scourage for perjury⟦br⟧
Can this dark <qex>monarchy</qex> afford false Clarence.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fifth monarchy</b></col>, <cd>a universal monarchy,
supposed to be the subject of prophecy in Daniel ii.; the four preceding
monarchies being Assyrian, Persian, Grecian, and Roman. See <cref>Fifth
Monarchy men</cref>, under <er>Fifth</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>monarda</ent>⟦br⟧
